{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d1083f74-d053-4fa1-9b7e-d2c253d2ed16","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\n> **Note:** For xUnit `[Theory]` tests, use `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` — the skip reason is a property on the test attribute itself, not a separate attribute.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2749f3a7-ff86-4412-8625-ae00a476b39b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no need to search the codebase.","outputTokens":313,"requestId":"4C19:20599D:B2358B:DDFC61:6A012D4F"},"id":"7e816dff-2a8a-4de9-924d-b3904fe0a706","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:13:58.109Z","parentId":"55e3792d-4b25-407c-b4ff-88d65106f92f"}
